HEADWORD: Strass
<hw>Strass</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from its
inventor, a German jeweler: cf. F. <ets>stras</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A brilliant glass, used in the manufacture of
artificial paste gems, which consists essentially of a complex
borosilicate of lead and potassium. Cf. <er>Glass</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

